.th GSCRL VII 19-March-1980
.sh NAME
gscrl \*- scroll GRINNELL display
.sh SYNOPSIS
int
.bd gscrl
(area, num, updown)
.s3
int area[16];
.br
int num;
.br
int updown;
.sh DESCRIPTION
.it Gscrl
is used to scroll the display up or down. As  many  as  512
rows  may  be  scrolled at one time. Scrolling the image could be
used when a continuous strip display is wanted.
.s1
The
.it area
parameter is the buffer used in the
.it gopen
call.
.it Num
is the number of lines to scroll, and
.it updown
indicates whether to scroll up (zero) or down (non-zero).
.s3
The value returned is zero if the call succeeded, non-zero if it failed.
